Package: SteamR
Title: Steam API for R
Version: 0.0.0.4
Authors@R: person("Andrew", "Lake", email = "lakegm@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Retrieves data from Valve's Steam network. Steam is an internet based game distribution network, 
            it hold data about games and users. Steam API is a way of accessing that data. This package uses 
            the API to get the data in R. A steam API key is needed for most of the functions and can be obtained
            from https://steamcommunity.com/dev/apikey.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.2)
Imports: data.table,
      rjson
License: GPL-2
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Suggests: testthat
